UMS configuration variables
===========================

   Most of the options are configured using the @{"UMS" Link "UMS"} variables which are
explained in this section.


Mandantory variables:

 @{" rfc.domainname " Link "rfc.domainname"}    Domain name for your system
 @{" rfc.username " Link "rfc.username"}      Account name for a local UMS RFC user

Optional variables (may be omitted):

 @{" rfc.dstime " Link "rfc.dstime"}        Daylight Saving Time on/off
 @{" rfc.export. " Link "rfc.export."}       Address conversions during message export
 @{" rfc.import. " Link "rfc.import."}       Address conversions during message import
 @{" rfc.mailencoding " Link "rfc.mailencoding"}  Encoding of mail message texts during export
 @{" rfc.newsencoding " Link "rfc.newsencoding"}  Encoding of news message texts during export
 @{" rfc.noownfqdn " Link "rfc.noownfqdn"}     The system has no own domain name
 @{" rfc.pathname " Link "rfc.pathname"}      Path name for your system
 @{" nntpd.access " Link "nntpd.access"}      Access rights for remote NNTP clients
 @{" nntpd.log " Link "nntpd.log"}         NNTP server log on/off
 @{" nntpget.groups " Link "nntpget.groups"}    Group list for news message import
 @{" smtpd.log " Link "smtpd.log"}         SMTP server log on/off

Mandantory UUCP variables:

 @{" uucp.mailexport " Link "uucp.mailexport"}   Configuration for mail batches
 @{" uucp.newsexport " Link "uucp.newsexport"}   Configuration for news batches
 @{" uucp.nodename " Link "uucp.nodename"}     UUCP node name for your system

Optional UUCP variables (may be omitted):

 @{" uucp.envelope " Link "uucp.envelope"}     UUCP envelope type
 @{" uucp.keepdupes " Link "uucp.keepdupes"}    Keep dupe messages
 @{" uucp.logdupes " Link "uucp.logdupes"}     Log dupe messages
 @{" uucp.mailroute " Link "uucp.mailroute"}    Mail routing configuration
 @{" uucp.recipients " Link "uucp.recipients"}   Limit number of recipients


