UUCP importer
=============

   The command @{b}uuxqt@{ub} imports mail and news messages from batch files
which were transferred via @{"UUCP" Link "UUCP"} from a remote host. This command is
normally only executed by the @{"UUCP" Link "UUCP"} transfer program @{b}uucico@{ub}.

     Syntax:
     
             uuxqt [-p <UMS password>]
                   [-d <n>]
                   [<subdirectory>]
     
     Defaults:
     
                    -p  No password
                    -d  0

   Explanation of the command line options:

@{b}-p@{ub}
     Password for the UMS user. This will be used for @{i}ALL@{ui} logins.

@{b}-d@{ub}
     UUCP log level: 0, 1, 2 or 3.

@{b}subdirectory@{ub}
     Name of the subdirectory in the @{"UUCP" Link "UUCP"} spool directory. This
     parameter is supplied by @{b}uucico@{ub} when a hierarchical spool
     directory structure is used.

   @{b}uuxqt@{ub} uses the following system for the @{"UMS user names" Link "Users"}:

     uucp.default  Used as the first login to read the configuration.
     
     uucp.<name>   Used when importing a batch from node @{b}name@{ub}.


@EndNode

