Telser configuration
====================

   The file @{b}AMITCP:db/telser.conf@{ub} describes the configuration for every
unit of the @{b}telser.device@{ub}. For the unit 0 it should look like this:

     0  ""    NoOperation NOOPENWIN NOLINGER NODEBUG T:telser.log


@EndNode

@Node "Hosts" "umsrfc.guide/Hosts"
@Prev "Telser"
@Toc "Examples"

Host descriptions
=================

   The file @{b}AMITCP:db/telser.hosts@{ub} contains the descriptions of the
remote systems. If you @{i}dial@{ui} a remote system using the @{b}telser.device@{ub} it
looks into this file to find out the hostname and the parameters. For
our example system it looks like this:

     dummy    dummy.do.main  540   ""    00000000001

   Please make sure that the 11th bit is set, because it activates the
transparent mode of @{b}telser.device@{ub} which is a @{i}must@{ui} for @{"UUCP" Link "UUCP"} over @{"TCP-IP" Link "TCP-IP"}.


@EndNode

