Solutions to common UMS RFC problems
************************************

@{b}Error: No rfc.username for...@{ub}
     You have forgotten to add the variable @{"rfc.username" Link "rfc.username"} to the user
     entry of a lokal user.

@{b}Error: Can't write article, check WRITEACCESS!@{ub}
     UMS RFC couldn't write the article to @{i}any@{ui} newsgroup. You have
     requested a newsgroup but forgotten to add it to the @{b}WRITEACCESS@{ub}
     patter of the importer entry. If you are receiving control
     messages you must also add the newsgroup @{b}rfc.control@{ub} to this
     pattern!

@{b}Error: Can't get connection data!@{ub}
     You forgot to update the service file of your AmiTCP installation.
     See @{"Services" Link "Services"}.

   You should also read the FAQ about @{"UMS" Link "UMS"}.


@EndNode

