History of UMS RFC
******************

   The following list gives an overview of all the changes since the
first version of UMS RFC: For more detailed information read the file
@{b}UMS/Networks/RFC/src/History@{ub}.

@{i}1.0 (20-Feb-1999)@{ui}
        - New version scheme taken into use. Changes in the library
          interface should be less error-prone now.

        - Now all LFs are converted to CR-LF as required by the @{"RFC 822" Link "Message Formats"}
          format, except for unbatched UUCP mail messages or UUCP news
          messages. All tools convert CR-LF to LF before importing the
          messages.

        - @{"ESMTP" Link "SMTP"} extensions PIPELINING and 8BITMIME implemented.

        - @{"NNTP" Link "NNTP"} extensions @{b}XOVER@{ub} and @{b}LIST OVERVIEW.FMT@{ub} implemented in
          the server. The clients now support the @{b}AUTHINFO USER/PASS@{ub}
          authentication extension.

        - Implemented some support for TaylorUUCP in The @{"UUCP" Link "UUCP"} tools.

        - Added new tool @{"umsrfcwrite" Link "umsrfcwrite"} for importing RFC messages.

        - The variable @{b}uucp.dumbhost@{ub} has been replace with the variable
          @{"uucp.envelope" Link "uucp.envelope"}. This might require a change to your UMS
          configuration.

        - The variables @{b}uucp.debug@{ub}, @{b}uucp.debugfile@{ub} and @{b}uucp.filtercr@{ub}
          have been removed.

        - @{"RFC" Link "RFC"} times is now converted to local time.

        - Several bug fixes.

@{i}0.12 (24-Mar-1996)@{ui}
        - Library interface changed. Please make sure that you only use
          the programs and library of this version together.

        - Support for systems without own domain name added, see
          @{"rfc.noownfqdn" Link "rfc.noownfqdn"}.  The variable @{b}rfc.receivedname@{ub} has been
          removed.

        - The variable @{"rfc.pathname" Link "rfc.pathname"} is now optional.

        - Support for @{"ESMTP" Link "SMTP"} added. Currently implemented is the SIZE
          extension.

        - Added new tool @{"umsrfcprint" Link "umsrfcprint"} for printing RFC messages.

        - Added Installer script.

        - Several bug fixes.

@{i}0.11 (09-Dec-1995)@{ui}
        - @{"POP3" Link "POP3"} server daemon @{"umspop3d" Link "umspop3d"}.

        - Support for UMS' binary field.

        - Implemented UUCP grades. The format of the variables
          @{"uucp.mailexport" Link "uucp.mailexport"} and @{"uucp.newsexport" Link "uucp.newsexport"} was changed!

        - Implemented CTRL-C handling for @{"umsnntpget" Link "umsnntpget"}.

        - Command logging for @{"NNTP" Link "NNTP"} and @{"SMTP" Link "SMTP"} server daemons.

        - Switch for Daylight Saving Time.

        - Several bug fixes and new command switches.

@{i}0.10 (04-Jun-1995)@{ui}
        - First official release of the UMS RFC package the successor
          of the UMS UUCP package.

        - All RFC from/to UMS conversions are handled by the
          @{b}umsrfc.library@{ub} now.

        - Support for @{"NNTP" Link "NNTP"}, @{"POP3" Link "POP3"}, @{"SMTP" Link "SMTP"}, @{"UUCP" Link "UUCP"}.

        - New documentation.

   For all older versions please read the file @{b}History@{ub} in the source
directory.


@EndNode

